lame two problems . first problem . let 's say you 're the typical kidnapper-rapist-killer . for fun and out of postmodern boredom , you kidnap two girls off the street in new york city . what are the odds that your randomly-chosen getaway and killing spot is going to be exactly where one of the girls lives , 60 or 70 miles away ? one in ten million ? twenty million ? second problem . the movie , even with a run time of an otherwise-short 84 minutes , does n't have enough action or development to fill the void . in short , it 's boring , and in several scenes where craven seems more interested in the bucolic wechester county scenery than moving the plot along , i found myself reaching for the fast-forward